verbose_text: Mutations in the ENG gene cause the autosomal dominant disorder hereditary hemorrhagic telangiectasia type 1 (HHT1), a vascular dysplasia with life threatening consequences that affects 1 in 10,000 individuals and is characterized by arteriovenous malformations, recurrent hemorrhages, and numerous sequelae.
